'''Zoophagia''' is a [[fiction|fictional]] [[psychology|psychological condition]] with which the character Renfield is afflicted in the [[novel]] [[Dracula]]. The condition is named by Dr. Seward and consists of the belief that if you eat live animals you gain their lifeforce onto your own.
The way Renfield attempts to extend his own life is that he gathers a great many flies then gathers a great number of spiders whom he feeds the flies to. The spiders are then fed to a great number of sparrows. The experiment was ceased after the sparrows despite Dr. Seward offering Reinfield a cat. At many points the cycle is interrupted and he is forced to devour all in a hurry. Whether the Zoophagia was caused by Renfield's servitude to Dracula or was a preexisting condition which made him more susceptible to the Count's power is never revealed.